724378f-a.title: Manhattan: West Broadway - Leonard Street
724378f-a.text:
West Broadway, west side, south from Leonard to
Worth Street's, showing a row of low structures (No's.
186 to 170 inclusive) overshadowed by the 24-storied
Western Union Building. The latter occupies the entire
block to the south, Worth to Thomas Street's, west to Hudson.
The side shown here is the Worth Street frontage. At the
right margin is a garage bearing No. 24-32 Leonard Street.
July 12, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
